tinyvmm is a very simple vmm to run a linux kernel bzImage and print the kernel
logs to the terminal. Only supports x86.

tinyvmm only implements bare minimum ttyS0 serial console support for redirecting
the kernel logs to stdout. It uses linux kvm to run the bzImage in a virtual
machine in an x86 machine.

Some references I used:
https://bellard.org/tinyemu/
https://lwn.net/Articles/658511/
https://gist.github.com/zserge/ae9098a75b2b83a1299d19b79b5fe488